              Yay for the onion haters! That leaves more for me!!<br /><br />Now we know why sweetpepper isn't called sweetonion. <img src="//cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/images/smilies/razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz Animated" /><br /><br />There's a middle-eastern dish called... mujadara that is rice, lentils and caramelized onions. It is one of my favorite comfort foods. Easy to make, good for you, and full of tasty onion.<br /><br />If you have a spare 8 hours, caramelizing onions in a crock pot is ideal. Toss them in, with a dab of butter or olive oil and a tablespoon or so of water set crock pot to low, cover and walk away. Stir them every hour or so. Perfect onions for french onion soup.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
